choices.text:
all the b.s. that made me think I have to be something that I’m not.Our schooling system is throwing out all the creativity of the younger generations.During my 13 years of education I personally discovered my passion for biology only at 12 and meanwhile everything I liked was ridiculed.Quality time in school was unbearable, you had zero social time there.It was always a lie, how everybody is equal and everybody matters.It was high school when I realized that teachers is for people who are dumb and weak, of for people who cannot be educated outside the system.This year I gave up the exams and natural talents sucked inside, because I’m tired of the system.
